						<summary>

						<p>On broken stones (three pieces) kept at the Saptamātrikā temple near the tank.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājakēsarivarman (Sundarachōḷa) Year 3: 960 A.D.</hi> </p>						

						<p>Records the gift of two plots of land amounting to three <hi rend="italic">mā, nāṭṭār-peruñchey</hi> and <hi rend="italic">nāṟṟukkāl tuḍarchchey</hi> for the maintenance of the tank <hi rend="italic">(kuḷappaṭṭi)</hi> at Vayalōkam in Vayalaka-nāḍu by the sword regiment Vīrachōḷa Ilaṅgōvēḷār <hi rend="italic">(Vīrachōḻa Ilaṅgōvēḷārvāḷpaḍai)</hi> and the body-guard unit <hi rend="italic">uḍanilai-chēvagar.</hi> It is also stated that these two plots of land were made over to the tank perpetually.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Āvaṇam</hi> Vol. No. 10 (1999) p. 15.</p>						

						</summary>
